# Adapter Implementation Pattern

## Contract Compliance

- Every adapter MUST implement its corresponding interface from `src/core/types.ts`
- Use `implements IStorageAdapter` or `implements INetworkAdapter` explicitly
- All interface methods must be implemented - no partial adapters

## Constructor Injection

```typescript
// Adapters receive platform dependencies via constructor
export class IndexedDBAdapter implements IStorageAdapter {
  constructor(private readonly dbName: string, private readonly version?: number) {}
}
```

## Error Wrapping

- Catch platform-specific errors and wrap in `StorageError` or `NetworkError`
- Include the original error as `cause` for debugging
- Never let platform exceptions leak to Core

```typescript
try {
  await db.put(storeName, value, key);
} catch (cause) {
  throw new StorageError(`Failed to set key "${key}"`, { cause });
}
```

## Platform Guards

- Web adapters may check for API availability: `typeof indexedDB !== 'undefined'`
- RN adapters may check for native module availability
- Throw descriptive errors if platform APIs are missing

## Memory Adapter

- `MemoryAdapter` is the reference implementation and test double
- Must pass all the same tests as platform adapters
- Uses plain `Map<string, unknown>` internally
